35 LAW ENFORCEMENT PROFILING
36
37 SECTION 6. ORS 131.915 is amended to read:
38 131.915. As used in ORS 131.915 to 131.925:
39 (1) “Gender identity” has the meaning given that term in ORS 174.100.
40 (2) “Law enforcement agency” means:
41 (a) The Department of State Police;
42 (b) The Department of Justice;
43 (c) A district attorney’s office; and
44 (d) Any of the following that maintains a law enforcement unit as defined in ORS 181A.355:
45 (A) A political subdivision or an instrumentality of the State of Oregon.
[4]

HB 4111
1 (B) A municipal corporation of the State of Oregon.
2 (C) A tribal government.
3 (D) A university.
4 (3) “Law enforcement officer” means:
5 (a) A member of the Oregon State Police;
6 (b) A sheriff, constable, marshal, municipal police officer or reserve officer or a police officer
7 commissioned by a university under ORS 352.121 or 353.125;
8 (c) An investigator of a district attorney’s office if the investigator is or has been certified as
9 a law enforcement officer in this or any other state;
10 (d) An investigator of the Criminal Justice Division of the Department of Justice;
11 (e) A humane special agent as defined in ORS 181A.345;
12 (f) A judicial marshal of the Marshal’s Office of the Judicial Department who is appointed under
13 ORS 1.177 and trained pursuant to ORS 181A.540;
14 (g) A regulatory specialist exercising authority described in ORS 471.775 (2); or
15 (h) An authorized tribal police officer as defined in ORS 181A.940.
16 (4) “Profiling” means the targeting of an individual by a law enforcement agency or a law
17 enforcement officer, on suspicion of the individual’s having violated a provision of law, based solely
18 on the individual’s real or perceived age, race, ethnicity, color, national origin, immigration status,
19 language, sex, gender identity, sexual orientation, political affiliation, religion, homelessness or dis-
20 ability, unless the agency or officer is acting on a suspect description or information related to an
21 identified or suspected violation of a provision of law.
22 (5) “Sexual orientation” has the meaning given that term in ORS 174.100.
23 SECTION 7. ORS 131.930 is amended to read:
24 131.930. As used in ORS 131.930 to 131.945:
25 (1) “Gender identity” has the meaning given that term in ORS 174.100.
26 (2) “Law enforcement agency” means an agency employing law enforcement officers to enforce
27 criminal laws.
28 (3) “Law enforcement officer” means a member of the Oregon State Police, a sheriff or a mu-
29 nicipal police officer.
30 (4) “Officer-initiated pedestrian stop” means a detention of a pedestrian by a law enforcement
31 officer that is not associated with a call for service. The term does not apply to detentions for
32 routine searches performed at the point of entry to or exit from a controlled area.
33 (5) “Officer-initiated traffic stop” means a detention of a driver of a motor vehicle by a law
34 enforcement officer, not associated with a call for service, for the purpose of investigating a sus-
35 pected violation of the Oregon Vehicle Code.
36 (6) “Profiling” means the targeting of an individual by a law enforcement agency or a law
37 enforcement officer, on suspicion of the individual’s having violated a provision of law, based solely
38 on the individual’s real or perceived age, race, ethnicity, color, national origin, immigration status,
39 language, sex, gender identity, sexual orientation, political affiliation, religion, homelessness or dis-
40 ability, unless the agency or officer is acting on a suspect description or information related to an
41 identified or suspected violation of a provision of law.
42 (7) “Sexual orientation” has the meaning given that term in ORS 174.100.
43 SECTION 8. The unit captions used in this 2026 Act are provided only for the convenience
44 of the reader and do not become part of the statutory law of this state or express any leg-
45 islative intent in the enactment of this 2026 Act.
